top:8px;float:right;">  	<img src="http://sentencedict.com/wordimage/147.jpg" style="width:300px;height:210px;" />  	<div style="text-align:center;margin-top:4px;font-size:12px;line-height:normal;margin-bottom:0px;width:280px;">Sentencedict.com random good picture</div>  </div>    <!--如果仅显示学生,并且该页有学生句子-->  <div id="all" >  <div>1. The fowler’s pipe sounds sweet until the <em>bird</em> is caught.&nbsp;<a href='/s/41955.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>2. Time is a <em>bird</em> for ever on the wing.&nbsp;<a href='/s/47005.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>3. It is an ill <em>bird</em> that fouls [soils] its own nest.&nbsp;<a href='/s/41249.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>4. Every <em>bird</em> likes its own nest.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42773.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>5. No <em>bird</em> soars too high, if he soars with his own wings.&nbsp;<a href='/s/46922.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>6. Each <em>bird</em> likes to hear himself sing.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40766.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>7. The noisy fowler catches no <em>bird</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42005.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div id="ad_marginbottom_0" style="margin-top:-10px;margin-bottom:5px;"><script async src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script><!-- 728_90_20170421 --><ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:inline-block;width:728px;height:90px" data-ad-client="ca-pub-7200850114163593" data-ad-slot="2392632666"></ins><script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script></div><div>8. A <em>bird</em> is known by its note, and a man by his talk.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40248.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>9. The <em>bird</em> that can sing and won’t sing must be made to sing.&nbsp;<a href='/s/41916.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>10. It is a dirty [foolish] <em>bird</em> that fouls [soils] its own nest.&nbsp;<a href='/s/41239.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>11. It's the early <em>bird</em> that catches the worm.&nbsp;<a href='/s/47991.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>12. A <em>bird</em> may be known by its song.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42387.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>13. A <em>bird</em> in the hand is worth two in the bush.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40247.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>14. It is an ill <em>bird</em> that fouls its own nest.&nbsp;<a href='/s/43153.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>15. The crow thinks his own <em>bird</em> fairest.&nbsp;<a href='/s/41930.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>16. The early <em>bird</em> catches the worm.&nbsp;<a href='/s/43801.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>17. ’Tis the early <em>bird</em> that catches the worm.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42148.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>18. He that will take the <em>bird</em> must not scare it.&nbsp;<a href='/s/41099.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>18. Sentencedict.com is a sentence dictionary, on which you can find nice sentences for a large number of words.</div><div>19. Every <em>bird</em> likes its own nest (best).&nbsp;<a href='/s/40793.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>20. Each <em>bird</em> loves to hear himself sing.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42757.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>21. An old <em>bird</em> is not to be caught with chaff.</div><div>22. Crane is a kind of <em>bird</em> with very long legs and neck.</div><div>23. The <em>bird</em> flapped its wings and flew away.</div><div>24. That <em>bird</em> tried to peck the baby.</div><div>25. The little <em>bird</em> is eating a grain of rice.</div><div>26. The <em>bird</em> flapped its wings furiously.</div><div>27. Is it cruel to confine a <em>bird</em> in a cage?</div><div>28. The male <em>bird</em> performs a sort of mating dance before copulating with the female.</div><div>29. It is not only the feather that makes the <em>bird</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/41290.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div style="margin-bottom:3px;">30. As the house is to the man, so is the nest to the <em>bird</em